IDE/TOOL SHORTCUTS

Eclipse shortcuts
1. ctrl+cmd+//  -> /* multiline comment */
2. sysout and Ctrl+Space
3. Mac OS X(switching between tabs in eclipse editor):
       Fn+Cntrl+↑
       Fn+Cntrl+↓
Formats code - CTRL + SHIFT + F
command+o  : method search in a class
cmd+shift : text selection
F3 : directly to method definition from cursor placed at call
cmd+shift+f - auto format
cmd+shift+l = keycap
Ctrl + 1 for quick fix


Intellij
cntrl+cmd+l = code format
mvn clean install -U
mvn clean idea:idea
Shortcuts
1.  fn+cmd+left arrow/right arrow : start and end of file
2. ⌃Y Delete current line
3. shift+alt + left arrow/right arrow Select previous/next word
4. Cmd + F12  - structure pop up
5.


iTerm2
1. cmd-d and cmd-shift-d divide an existing session vertically or horizontally
2. navigate among split panes with cmd-opt-arrow or cmd-[ and cmd-].
3. Autocomplete -  press cmd-;
4. access paste history with cmd-shift-H
End the search at current history entry	Ctrl + Y
Cmd  + enter - maximise window



